{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778176265,"nonce":"R5CzkyuTzAvU4LAqZ86xBgpEIFw=","message":"**Induced-gain analyser landed** (issue `74bfd86`, commit `ac84c78`, auth `59f9ea51`).\n\n`src/rlrmp/analysis/induced_gain.py` computes `||T_{w→z}||_∞` for any controller (LTI Riccati/LQR, or trained nonlinear RNN via feedbax adapter) on a given plant. Three `w` channels (`additive_force` flavor (a), `sensory_noise`, `structural_da` flavor (b)), four `z` channels (`qr_cost` headline + `control`, `state_error`, `peak_velocity`), two algorithms (LTV power iteration + LTI Hamiltonian-via-bounded-real-Riccati).\n\n**Why this is a cross-cutting state change:** (1) it's the synthesis_review §11 step-2 instrument — the cheapest scalar diagnostic for evaluating flavor (a) ⊊ (b) on existing networks, runnable across all Part 2.5 checkpoints in seconds each post-build; (2) the `structural_da` channel via small-gain framing means the (a) ⊊ (b) test does *not* require flavor-(b)-trained networks — it can be measured on networks we already have. (3) Multiple existing analyses become subsumable as decorations of the induced-gain output (cost-channel `||T||` *is* the operator-norm answer to several disturbance-rejection questions previously framed as separate analyses).\n\n**Tier guess:** essential. Concrete tier-shift discussion deferred until first run on real checkpoints surfaces actual numbers — that comment will live here too with the runs that produce it.\n\n**Known limitations / follow-ups** (only file as separate issues if they become load-bearing):\n- `qr_cost` × non-`additive_force` channel combinations have conservatively zeroed feedthrough.\n- `feedbax_rnn_controller` adapter needs a pure step-closure from the caller; deeper feedbax-`Iterator` integration is a likely friction point.\n- Riccati exact round-trip identity is approximate (`||T||_PI ≈ 0.92 · γ*` at bisection boundary; finite-horizon LQ-game effect, not a bug).\n\nCompanion analyses on the methodology-fix child list: `97c227a` (Riccati flavor-(b) extension), `c723082` (LinearDynamicsAdversary training side), `db35426` (Riccati teacher distillation), `2e5f643` (damping calibration), `a5e1450` (cross-partial).","files":null}]}